					<!--For Release 8:00 a.m. PST, July 31, 2000:-->
					<br><br>
					<font size="2" face="verdana, arial"><b><i>Fountain Valley, CA (July 31, 2000) --</i></b> 
					Kingston<sup>&#174;</sup> Technology Co. Inc., a leading supplier of PC peripherals, 
					today announced the release of its new high-speed networking kit based on IDG Books 
					Worldwide's Networking For Dummies<sup>&#174;</sup>.  Designed for non-technical 
					users, Kingston's high-speed networking kit is the easiest solution for connecting 
					multiple systems together in the home.  Kingston's networking kit comes with a 
					custom, easy-to-follow installation guide, based on IDGB's leading For 
					Dummies<sup>&#174;</sup> technical reference guides. 
					<br><br>
					As home networks become increasingly popular, the need for easy to implement 
					networking solutions is growing.  IDC estimates that by 2004, sixty-three percent of U.S. 
					households will possess a PC, while nearly half of these homes will house more than 
					one computer.  IDC data further indicates that more than half of the multi-PC homes 
					will network their devices within the next four years.
					<br><br>
					"With the proliferation of home computers, more and more households are 
					opting for a networked environment," said Andy Goldberg, product manager, 
					Peripheral Products Division.  "Our findings suggest that sixty percent of homes 
					are utilizing more than one electronic device that have yet to be networked.  
					The most common reason for a user's reluctance to install a network is the 
					fear of not having performed the task before.  Our goal is to provide solutions 
					that are user-friendly to the non-technical home user," added Goldberg.
					<br><br>
					By partnering with IDG Books, Kingston is able to leverage IDGB's expertise in 
					demystifying technology and other complex topics.  IDGB consistently occupies 
					a majority of the Publishers Weekly Computer Bestseller list, a nationally 
					recognized barometer of book sales.  Kingston and IDGB co-developed a 
					new "High-speed Networking Kit" installation guide which takes the user 
					step-by-step through the plug-n-play installation process in the straight 
					forward, easy-to-understand way that the award winning authors of the 
					For Dummies series are known for.
					<br><br>
					Kingston's High-Speed Networking Kit includes everything needed to connect 
					home PCs for shared Internet access, files and printing. The High-Speed 
					Networking kit is also compatible with Windows&#153; 98, NT, and 2000.  
					With switched Fast Ethernet connections of up to 200Mbps, it provides 
					all the bandwidth needed for today's data intensive file sharing and 
					network gaming. Kingston's High-Speed Networking Kit includes:
					<ul>
					<li>5-port 10/100TX workgroup switch</li>
					<li>Two 10/100TX PCI Fast Ethernet adapters with Wake on LAN</li>
					<li>Two category-5UTP cables</li>
					<li>High-speed Networking Kit For Dummies<sup>&#174;</sup> installation guide</li>
					<li>Star Tech Internet sharing software</li>
					<li>A coupon for a free Networking For Dummies<sup>&#174;</sup> book</li>
					</ul>
					Kingston's High-Speed Networking Kit, part number: KNB2501TXD, has a 
					Manufacturer's Suggested Retail Price (MSRP) of $169.00 and is available through 
					leading E-tailers.  Kingston's Peripheral products are individually tested and 
					backed by an extensive warranty.  Technical support is comprehensive, staffed 
					by certified network engineers and provided free of charge.
